1
00:00:17,768 --> 00:00:20,398
Do you even know what I've been through to get here?

2
00:00:20,798 --> 00:00:23,098
I will not fall because of a punk like you!

3
00:00:36,598 --> 00:00:38,238
By any chance,

4
00:00:40,338 --> 00:00:42,068
did you use to be a ghost writer yourself too?

5
00:00:46,139 --> 00:00:47,839
(Episode 5)

6
00:01:03,899 --> 00:01:07,169
Until when will you be conscious of Se Ju when you write?

7
00:01:07,769 --> 00:01:10,169
If you are not confident to surpass the person you imitated,

8
00:01:10,269 --> 00:01:12,199
don't even try to imitate him from the start.

9
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,470
What are you reading?

10
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:27,200
Oh, I'm sorry.

11
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,240
I saw it on your desk and just got curious.

12
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,040
What is it?

13
00:01:39,171 --> 00:01:40,241
Keep reading.

14
00:01:44,641 --> 00:01:45,801
Can I read it?

15
00:01:45,841 --> 00:01:47,771
Why are you even asking?

16
00:01:47,871 --> 00:01:50,171
You've always been the first to read everything I write.

17
00:01:50,671 --> 00:01:52,701
You get cranky about it at times though.

18
00:01:53,771 --> 00:01:55,171
I guess you're confident about this one.

19
00:01:56,141 --> 00:01:58,071
You can pick up your stick after reading it,

20
00:01:58,242 --> 00:02:00,772
but give me some carrots here and there while reading it too.

21
00:02:01,272 --> 00:02:05,572
I know that criticism helps me grow and improve, but it does hurt.

22
00:02:05,942 --> 00:02:07,912
Goodness, you're such a cry baby.

23
00:02:36,142 --> 00:02:38,002
- How is it? - What?

24
00:02:38,272 --> 00:02:39,672
I'm asking what you think about it.

25
00:02:41,672 --> 00:02:44,002
Hey, I'm just on the fourth page now.

26
00:02:45,058 --> 00:02:48,058
That's no good. That tells it all.

27
00:02:49,158 --> 00:02:52,128
It's a fail if the reader isn't captivated by the first two pages.

28
00:02:52,428 --> 00:02:54,288
I mean, it's only a short story.

29
00:02:54,858 --> 00:02:57,758
I shouldn't show it to Mr. Baek.

30
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:03,228
Were you planning on showing this to my dad?

31
00:03:03,358 --> 00:03:04,958
He told me to bring it.

32
00:03:05,888 --> 00:03:07,358
But I probably shouldn't.

33
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:12,258
I can tell from the look on your face that he'll say nothing nice.

34
00:03:18,688 --> 00:03:21,258
Did you write Baek Tae Min's "Fate" for him?

35
00:03:22,158 --> 00:03:24,128
Were you his ghost writer?

36
00:03:29,628 --> 00:03:30,728
Get out.

37
00:03:38,028 --> 00:03:39,088
I...

38
00:03:40,358 --> 00:03:42,888
I'd much rather let someone steal my writing...

39
00:03:44,188 --> 00:03:45,958
than taking credit for someone else's work.

40
00:04:11,228 --> 00:04:12,958
("Fate")

41
00:04:21,488 --> 00:04:22,788
Where have you been?

42
00:04:24,758 --> 00:04:28,988
I didn't even know you left. I'm asking where you were!

43
00:04:30,528 --> 00:04:33,358
Can you not hear me? Am I invisible to you?

44
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,488
Or are you pretending you can't hear me?

45
00:04:37,988 --> 00:04:40,528
Do you spend all of your time trying to figure out a way...

46
00:04:40,528 --> 00:04:44,698
to make me more miserable instead of writing when you're stuck here?

47
00:04:45,028 --> 00:04:48,028
Don't ask me questions that are not worthy answering,

48
00:04:48,088 --> 00:04:49,698
and just cut to the chase.

49
00:04:54,488 --> 00:04:57,228
Try to find a day and time you're available.

50
00:04:58,458 --> 00:05:01,828
They're saying there's a big demand for a joint interview to promote it.

51
00:05:02,388 --> 00:05:04,128
You should help out because it's for your son.

52
00:05:04,358 --> 00:05:05,828
They're still pushing for it?

53
00:05:05,828 --> 00:05:08,058
He said no, but that obviously didn't work.

54
00:05:08,058 --> 00:05:10,928
He thought he should at least ask you what you think.

55
00:05:10,928 --> 00:05:13,198
That's why he turned around and came back after he left for his trip.

56
00:05:13,228 --> 00:05:15,788
- When is good for you? - I don't have any time for it.

57
00:05:16,128 --> 00:05:17,158
I can't do it.

58
00:05:17,758 --> 00:05:20,028
You can't? Why not?

59
00:05:20,888 --> 00:05:22,828
You can't even do that for your own son?

60
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,928
So is this what you're doing for your son's sake?

61
00:05:28,058 --> 00:05:31,928
Digging someone else's grave just to protect that third-rate novel?

62
00:05:33,328 --> 00:05:36,888
You know, you should just go shopping instead which you love.

63
00:05:37,028 --> 00:05:38,828
Or start painting again.

64
00:05:40,688 --> 00:05:41,958
What's wrong with it?

65
00:05:43,058 --> 00:05:47,088
That woman ruined my life, and her son...

66
00:05:47,158 --> 00:05:49,288
is blocking my son's future.

67
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,558
I can do anything.

68
00:05:53,288 --> 00:05:56,158
In this line of work, what matters is ability and talent.

69
00:05:56,628 --> 00:05:58,088
He has to shine on his own.

70
00:05:58,688 --> 00:06:00,988
If he needs my name to make a name for himself,

71
00:06:00,988 --> 00:06:04,158
he should quit writing for both of our sakes.

72
00:06:04,388 --> 00:06:05,528
That will be for the best.

73
00:06:24,288 --> 00:06:25,388
Seol.

74
00:06:26,788 --> 00:06:27,988
Go away.

75
00:06:29,328 --> 00:06:30,988
I can't play with you today.

76
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:38,888
Your debut novel, "Fate". I was so touched by it.

77
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:41,488
I guess you didn't like the novels I wrote after that.

78
00:06:42,428 --> 00:06:43,988
Oh, that's...

79
00:06:44,628 --> 00:06:46,188
Mr. Han Se Ju?

80
00:06:52,358 --> 00:06:54,558
Han Se Ju.

81
00:06:59,988 --> 00:07:02,528
Han Se Ju...

82
00:07:07,028 --> 00:07:08,128
Seol.

83
00:07:09,458 --> 00:07:10,858
Why are you being like this?

84
00:07:11,488 --> 00:07:13,288
I'm doing some thinking right now.

85
00:07:20,628 --> 00:07:22,458
I told you to go away.

86
00:07:23,988 --> 00:07:26,128
I said I can't play with you right now.

87
00:07:27,788 --> 00:07:29,228
Even you...

88
00:07:31,858 --> 00:07:34,028
are going to slight me?

89
00:07:36,128 --> 00:07:37,128
You can't.

90
00:07:39,328 --> 00:07:41,828
(Chicago Typewriter)

91
00:07:52,328 --> 00:07:54,158
Thank you for calling Do Anything. This is...

92
00:07:54,158 --> 00:07:56,188
I curse you, witch.

93
00:07:57,988 --> 00:08:00,028
- We love all of our customers. - You piece of...

94
00:08:00,028 --> 00:08:02,258
I'm going to pick your eyeballs out and throw them around.

95
00:08:02,258 --> 00:08:04,958
How dare you hover around Se Ju? A ghost writer?

96
00:08:05,088 --> 00:08:07,858
Shall I kill you so that you can actually become a ghost?

97
00:08:07,858 --> 00:08:11,928
My gosh, it doesn't sound like you enjoyed your school lunch today.

98
00:08:11,928 --> 00:08:14,958
Shut it! I have all of your personal information. You better watch out.

99
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:18,428
I'm going to plaster cement all over you the second I spot you.

100
00:08:20,988 --> 00:08:22,158
What a potty mouth.

101
00:08:34,758 --> 00:08:38,688
Do you think you're mentally invincible? Just ignore the calls.

102
00:08:38,688 --> 00:08:41,358
Give it back. It could be a customer calling.

103
00:08:41,358 --> 00:08:45,058
Customer, my foot. They're all crazy fans of Han Se Ju.

104
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:48,988
How many calls have you gotten today after the scandal broke out?

105
00:08:49,328 --> 00:08:51,158
25 calls.

106
00:08:51,828 --> 00:08:53,798
- Do you think it was a question? - No.

107
00:08:58,858 --> 00:09:02,028
My mom wasn't entirely wrong.

108
00:09:02,228 --> 00:09:04,958
She said something unfortunate might happen to you.

109
00:09:05,798 --> 00:09:08,828
You shouldn't have gotten involved with Han Se Ju.

110
00:09:10,298 --> 00:09:14,088
I think I betrayed my country in my past life.

111
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:15,988
What are you talking about?

112
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:19,128
Shooting, being a vet, and working for Do Anything.

113
00:09:19,228 --> 00:09:22,888
Whenever I try to do something, something stops me.

114
00:09:22,888 --> 00:09:24,928
You are so naive.

115
00:09:25,228 --> 00:09:28,658
The descendants of independent fighters live more poorly now.

116
00:09:28,658 --> 00:09:33,158
The descendants of the betrayers are richer and live better lives.

117
00:09:33,388 --> 00:09:34,688
If you wanted to be born rich,

118
00:09:34,688 --> 00:09:37,298
you should've been a pro-Japanese faction in the past life.

119
00:09:37,298 --> 00:09:38,328
Is that right?

120
00:09:39,688 --> 00:09:40,888
It sounds strangely convincing.

121
00:09:40,888 --> 00:09:43,028
I think it turned out well.

122
00:09:43,558 --> 00:09:46,688
You won't be able to turn this on now.

123
00:09:46,688 --> 00:09:48,458
Just use this chance to quit Do Anything...

124
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:49,888
and return to being a vet.

125
00:09:49,888 --> 00:09:52,228
You said your friend is going to make you the assistant director.

126
00:09:52,428 --> 00:09:54,758
I already decided to do that.

127
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:57,028
Really?

128
00:09:57,588 --> 00:09:59,228
Are you okay now?

129
00:09:59,228 --> 00:10:02,358
No, I will be working only Monday, Wednesday, and Friday for now.

130
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:03,958
I'm going to slowly adjust to it.

131
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:06,728
Good job. Good job.

132
00:10:06,988 --> 00:10:09,488
Let's celebrate it with some beer.

133
00:10:09,488 --> 00:10:11,188
Wait here. I'll be right back.

134
00:10:36,758 --> 00:10:38,258
Mr. Yoo?

135
00:10:45,628 --> 00:10:49,458
What are you doing here?

136
00:10:56,928 --> 00:10:59,928
Did you come to meet me?

137
00:10:59,928 --> 00:11:01,758
No, the towel.

138
00:11:10,258 --> 00:11:11,358
Darn it.

139
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:18,088
What brings you here?

140
00:11:19,488 --> 00:11:20,628
Actually,

141
00:11:21,128 --> 00:11:24,428
I got kicked out of my house after having an argument.

142
00:11:26,388 --> 00:11:27,588
Are you married?

143
00:11:28,758 --> 00:11:31,628
No. I am not taken yet.

144
00:11:33,628 --> 00:11:36,188
Should we go somewhere and get some beer?

145
00:11:37,928 --> 00:11:41,088
Is Jeon Seol asleep?

146
00:11:43,788 --> 00:11:45,988
Do you know Seol?

147
00:11:47,688 --> 00:11:50,988
Is Seol happy here?

148
00:11:55,458 --> 00:11:58,388
Wait here. I will call her.

149
00:11:59,358 --> 00:12:03,028
What? Wait. You don't have to...

150
00:12:48,688 --> 00:12:50,058
Your stance is unstable.

151
00:12:50,328 --> 00:12:51,858
You can't be afraid of the recoil.

152
00:12:51,858 --> 00:12:55,158
If you are, your body will move back or your arm will droop down.

153
00:12:55,658 --> 00:12:57,558
Then you lose stability and control.

154
00:13:00,928 --> 00:13:01,958
Aim for it.

155
00:13:07,428 --> 00:13:08,428
Fire.

156
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:16,158
What's this?

157
00:13:19,488 --> 00:13:22,128
Hey, Jeon Seol, go outside.

158
00:13:22,688 --> 00:13:24,288
Someone came for you.

159
00:13:25,528 --> 00:13:26,528
For me?

160
00:13:27,588 --> 00:13:29,928
- Who is it? - How would I know?

161
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:34,658
What's wrong with you?

162
00:13:37,988 --> 00:13:41,158
Hey! Your identity has gotten out, and yet you're fearless.

163
00:13:41,428 --> 00:13:42,688
You should wear a hat.

164
00:13:43,228 --> 00:13:44,228
Okay.

165
00:13:51,828 --> 00:13:53,128
You lucky wench.

166
00:13:53,888 --> 00:13:56,258
She must've betrayed her country a big time in her past life.

167
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:13,458
What? Who's looking for me?

168
00:14:59,058 --> 00:15:01,128
I am sorry.

169
00:15:01,628 --> 00:15:02,688
It's okay.

170
00:15:49,028 --> 00:15:50,058
Have you succeeded?

171
00:15:50,388 --> 00:15:52,288
Taking the eight 'o clock train bound for Sinuiju,

172
00:15:52,288 --> 00:15:55,028
Choi Min Gyo will deliver the campaign fund to Manchuria.

173
00:15:55,658 --> 00:15:57,228
Our head will be happy.

174
00:16:01,758 --> 00:16:04,088
A gunfight broke out sporadically.

175
00:16:05,828 --> 00:16:06,828
Let me see.

176
00:16:07,458 --> 00:16:09,228
You should stay away. The police are following me.

177
00:17:47,088 --> 00:17:50,388
I am sorry. If you're done watching,

178
00:17:50,388 --> 00:17:53,658
will you shut the door?

179
00:17:54,998 --> 00:17:58,128
The girls have to get changed to prepare for the performance.

180
00:18:01,428 --> 00:18:02,788
I am sorry.

181
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:06,788
This is a girl's changing room.

182
00:18:07,188 --> 00:18:09,458
We prepared a space for you.

183
00:18:18,628 --> 00:18:23,828
When I meet him, he always smell of hair oil

184
00:18:24,158 --> 00:18:29,158
Cuckoo cries sadly for fading Spring

185
00:18:29,428 --> 00:18:32,558
Crying and crying

186
00:18:35,088 --> 00:18:40,828
The wind blows and the spider web chokes my neck

187
00:18:40,828 --> 00:18:46,288
Oh dear, it hurts

188
00:18:46,498 --> 00:18:49,228
Please save me

189
00:18:49,228 --> 00:18:54,998
Please save me

190
00:19:05,028 --> 00:19:06,128
Seol.

191
00:19:06,858 --> 00:19:07,958
Seol.

192
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:09,558
Jeon Seol.

193
00:19:12,758 --> 00:19:14,428
Bang Wool.

194
00:19:16,458 --> 00:19:17,528
It...

195
00:19:18,158 --> 00:19:19,928
started again,

196
00:19:20,428 --> 00:19:21,628
right?

197
00:19:34,158 --> 00:19:36,028
"I killed someone."

198
00:19:37,288 --> 00:19:40,028
"I killed someone I shouldn't have killed."

199
00:19:40,028 --> 00:19:42,158
That's what you said when you were 10.

200
00:19:43,288 --> 00:19:47,658
That was so sudden. I wasn't ready to hear.

201
00:19:52,258 --> 00:19:55,558
- "I killed someone." - Why are you repeating it?

202
00:19:55,558 --> 00:19:57,888
You wanted to be ready.

203
00:19:57,888 --> 00:19:59,128
Forget it.

204
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:03,058
Why didn't Mom take me to a doctor?

205
00:20:03,458 --> 00:20:05,288
Why did she take me to a shaman?

206
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:07,058
Do you think she didn't take you to a doctor?

207
00:20:07,358 --> 00:20:11,788
The doctor said you were just too imaginative...

208
00:20:11,788 --> 00:20:15,858
and extremely intelligent.

209
00:20:15,998 --> 00:20:18,858
But your mom didn't believe it.

210
00:20:19,998 --> 00:20:22,558
What did you say to her then?

211
00:20:22,628 --> 00:20:25,288
I told her there was no chance of you becoming a shaman.

212
00:20:25,288 --> 00:20:26,428
Are you happy now?

213
00:20:27,058 --> 00:20:29,258
Was that all and you got paid?

214
00:20:29,258 --> 00:20:31,188
When you die,

215
00:20:32,088 --> 00:20:34,828
you cross the river of oblivion.

216
00:20:35,188 --> 00:20:36,958
You're making that up again.

217
00:20:40,028 --> 00:20:42,228
But if you have regrets about your life,

218
00:20:42,888 --> 00:20:44,758
have passion left inside you,

219
00:20:45,528 --> 00:20:49,028
or have unforgettable people or memories,

220
00:20:49,658 --> 00:20:51,258
you look back.

221
00:20:52,628 --> 00:20:57,158
You're not supposed to look back while crossing the river.

222
00:20:57,928 --> 00:21:00,858
It gives you residues of memories.

223
00:21:02,658 --> 00:21:03,888
Is that a punishment?

224
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:06,028
You can't really say that.

225
00:21:06,558 --> 00:21:10,288
As the memories are not perfect, you become afraid of them.

226
00:21:14,658 --> 00:21:16,228
I wonder...

227
00:21:17,358 --> 00:21:19,688
why I got residues of memories.

228
00:21:20,088 --> 00:21:21,628
What's the point of knowing that?

229
00:21:22,928 --> 00:21:25,688
Just live your life.

230
00:21:26,428 --> 00:21:29,728
In order to have no regrets, passion,

231
00:21:30,658 --> 00:21:33,028
or sad stories left inside you when you leave the world,

232
00:21:33,558 --> 00:21:36,728
do your best in your life.

233
00:21:42,558 --> 00:21:44,458
Was it regret...

234
00:21:45,358 --> 00:21:47,228
or passion?

235
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:50,828
Or...

236
00:21:51,928 --> 00:21:54,488
were there people or stories...

237
00:21:57,158 --> 00:21:59,028
I didn't want to forget...

238
00:21:59,828 --> 00:22:02,288
or I wasn't supposed to forget...

239
00:22:03,788 --> 00:22:05,328
even after I died?

240
00:22:47,558 --> 00:22:49,828
Even though we lost our country,

241
00:22:50,358 --> 00:22:53,188
no one can take my words away from me.

242
00:22:55,288 --> 00:22:57,458
If I can't write,

243
00:22:58,288 --> 00:23:00,628
I'll be no different from a ghost.

244
00:23:01,628 --> 00:23:03,758
When Joseon is liberated,

245
00:23:03,758 --> 00:23:07,328
I'll write whatever I want with passion.

246
00:23:12,288 --> 00:23:14,358
She's beautiful.

247
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:17,728
Aren't you going to watch the performance?

248
00:23:17,728 --> 00:23:18,788
I can't.

249
00:23:23,188 --> 00:23:25,258
The deadline is in an hour.

250
00:23:25,758 --> 00:23:27,928
You used to be praised as a genius.

251
00:23:27,928 --> 00:23:31,028
Are you going to keep writing those dime novels?

252
00:23:31,758 --> 00:23:33,058
Are you teasing me?

253
00:23:33,058 --> 00:23:37,758
I'm on the blacklist and there are eyes on me.

254
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,728
What else could I write?

255
00:23:40,258 --> 00:23:42,228
Is that why you're writing dime novels?

256
00:23:42,528 --> 00:23:44,328
Why don't you just give up writing altogether?

257
00:23:45,828 --> 00:23:47,858
Even though we lost our country,

258
00:23:49,658 --> 00:23:52,458
no one can take my words away from me.

259
00:23:53,888 --> 00:23:55,558
If I can't write,

260
00:23:56,888 --> 00:23:59,258
I'll be no different from a ghost.

261
00:24:00,058 --> 00:24:01,988
When Joseon is liberated,

262
00:24:03,828 --> 00:24:07,058
I'll write whatever I want with passion.

263
00:24:09,788 --> 00:24:13,558
I guess there will be no blacklist once Joseon is liberated.

264
00:24:13,858 --> 00:24:16,488
Of course not. That's what it means to be liberated.

265
00:24:17,958 --> 00:24:20,528
What about you? Aren't you going to start writing again?

266
00:24:20,988 --> 00:24:24,488
I don't think so. I think I'll start dating instead.

267
00:24:25,528 --> 00:24:26,858
Who are you going to date?

268
00:25:01,528 --> 00:25:03,028
Please keep writing.

269
00:25:04,928 --> 00:25:07,228
That novel has to be completed...

270
00:25:08,928 --> 00:25:10,158
for me...

271
00:25:12,088 --> 00:25:13,458
to live.

272
00:25:37,428 --> 00:25:39,458
Ms. Kang.

273
00:25:41,088 --> 00:25:44,858
You don't have to come here for the time being. Why are you here?

274
00:25:49,558 --> 00:25:50,828
Take a shower.

275
00:25:51,088 --> 00:25:52,688
I have something to tell you.

276
00:25:55,158 --> 00:25:56,958
What did you just say?

277
00:25:57,058 --> 00:25:59,188
I had someone look into it,

278
00:25:59,688 --> 00:26:04,388
and there have been transactions between Reporter Son and Ms. Hong.

279
00:26:05,088 --> 00:26:08,628
Reporter Son's malicious articles about you...

280
00:26:08,628 --> 00:26:10,888
must have something to do with the transactions.

281
00:26:15,058 --> 00:26:16,758
What would you like to do?

282
00:26:17,028 --> 00:26:20,158
Would you like to continue with the lawsuit?

283
00:26:28,988 --> 00:26:30,028
Mr. Han.

284
00:26:34,628 --> 00:26:35,928
Let's forget about it.

285
00:26:38,558 --> 00:26:39,858
I'll...

286
00:26:41,158 --> 00:26:42,458
withdraw the suit.

287
00:26:44,958 --> 00:26:46,488
Are you concerned about...

288
00:26:47,158 --> 00:26:48,428
Mr. Baek Do Ha?

289
00:26:49,188 --> 00:26:52,328
I see that you have something writers should not have.

290
00:26:52,788 --> 00:26:55,758
Wouldn't it be wise to get rid of things that could become problems?

291
00:26:55,858 --> 00:26:57,458
I'm just going to think that I didn't see it.

292
00:26:57,858 --> 00:26:59,028
Put this away.

293
00:26:59,658 --> 00:27:02,158
I know he used to be your teacher...

294
00:27:02,458 --> 00:27:04,288
and he's like a father to you.

295
00:27:04,558 --> 00:27:07,288
I understand you don't want to...

296
00:27:07,528 --> 00:27:09,628
- get him in trouble. - Thank you for your work.

297
00:27:10,158 --> 00:27:11,688
You can go home now.

298
00:27:13,258 --> 00:27:16,528
Mr. Gal seems to be preparing for a lawsuit using Ms. Jeon.

299
00:27:17,658 --> 00:27:19,428
Why don't we...

300
00:27:19,528 --> 00:27:20,728
Who is...

301
00:27:22,158 --> 00:27:23,688
using who?

302
00:27:35,158 --> 00:27:37,558
I'm sorry I kept you waiting.

303
00:27:38,028 --> 00:27:39,258
Well...

304
00:27:40,558 --> 00:27:42,958
I'm Gal Ji Seok at Golden Bear.

305
00:27:43,928 --> 00:27:47,158
I have no business cards. I'm Jeon Seol.

306
00:27:47,158 --> 00:27:49,628
- Please sit down. - Okay.

307
00:27:55,058 --> 00:27:56,788
You were very upset about the article, right?

308
00:27:57,188 --> 00:27:58,658
A bit.

309
00:27:59,528 --> 00:28:01,458
Is Mr. Han okay?

310
00:28:02,758 --> 00:28:06,888
I'm not sure. He says he's okay,

311
00:28:07,088 --> 00:28:09,358
but he's just a human being. I'm sure he got hurt.

312
00:28:09,358 --> 00:28:12,728
He must be frustrated and infuriated.

313
00:28:13,188 --> 00:28:15,488
Then why won't he make any statement about it?

314
00:28:16,558 --> 00:28:19,628
People won't believe what he says anyway.

315
00:28:19,628 --> 00:28:21,058
They'll just want to criticize him.

316
00:28:22,158 --> 00:28:24,028
They'll look at him like this.

317
00:28:26,088 --> 00:28:27,688
They'll do that.

318
00:28:28,658 --> 00:28:32,458
"I see." They never be nice like this.

319
00:28:33,458 --> 00:28:37,028
I'm neither his girlfriend nor his ghost writer.

320
00:28:37,028 --> 00:28:40,288
- I'm just a fan. - I know that.

321
00:28:40,288 --> 00:28:42,228
Reporter Son, that jerk...

322
00:28:44,728 --> 00:28:46,728
Yellow papers...

323
00:28:47,258 --> 00:28:49,658
don't care a bit about truths.

324
00:28:49,858 --> 00:28:52,658
Mr. Han himself denied it. How could he do this?

325
00:28:53,888 --> 00:28:55,958
On that note, Ms. Jeon, Let's teach...

326
00:28:56,558 --> 00:28:58,828
Reporter Son a serious lesson.

327
00:29:05,458 --> 00:29:08,488
What should we do to teach him a serious lesson?

328
00:29:10,788 --> 00:29:14,358
Let's shoot an awesome drama set in the court of law.

329
00:29:17,488 --> 00:29:20,288
Are you asking me to sue Reporter Son...

330
00:29:20,858 --> 00:29:22,928
in place of Mr. Han?

331
00:29:23,888 --> 00:29:27,588
You're so intelligent, and you understand things very quickly.

332
00:29:27,858 --> 00:29:30,728
We'll take care of all the legal fees, of course.

333
00:29:33,958 --> 00:29:35,028
Ms. Jeon.

334
00:29:35,188 --> 00:29:39,228
You saved Se Ju's life twice.

335
00:29:40,588 --> 00:29:42,388
Help him once more and make it three times.

336
00:29:44,258 --> 00:29:46,328
How does Mr. Han feel about it?

337
00:29:46,888 --> 00:29:50,658
I'm afraid that me getting involved might cause trouble for him...

338
00:29:50,888 --> 00:29:52,528
You don't need to worry about that.

339
00:29:52,688 --> 00:29:54,558
Se Ju thinks exactly what I think.

340
00:29:54,828 --> 00:29:56,828
- He and I always think... - That's what you think.

341
00:29:56,828 --> 00:29:58,628
Gosh, you totally startled me.

342
00:29:59,328 --> 00:30:03,128
I don't want to sue him. That's what I think.

343
00:30:04,088 --> 00:30:05,128
Well...

344
00:30:08,128 --> 00:30:09,158
Get up.

345
00:30:09,628 --> 00:30:10,958
We're talking right now.

346
00:30:10,958 --> 00:30:12,628
- Just get up. - Se Ju.

347
00:30:13,058 --> 00:30:15,828
Se Ju. Se Ju, please.

348
00:30:16,958 --> 00:30:18,388
I've clearly warned you.

349
00:30:19,428 --> 00:30:20,958
If you don't stop immediately,

350
00:30:21,788 --> 00:30:23,758
you and I will have to quit.

351
00:30:32,388 --> 00:30:35,488
What is he being like that? Is he back to being a moody stranger?

352
00:30:36,088 --> 00:30:38,228
Gosh, I'm getting acid reflux. Thanks.

353
00:30:39,428 --> 00:30:42,928
Hey, Doo Yeob. Delete that photo right now, okay?

354
00:30:44,128 --> 00:30:45,628
And all of you, get back to work!

355
00:30:52,828 --> 00:30:54,828
- Don't do it. - What?

356
00:30:55,188 --> 00:30:56,428
Don't sue him.

357
00:30:58,028 --> 00:31:00,258
No matter what Ji Seok tells you to coax you into it,

358
00:31:00,728 --> 00:31:02,528
don't do it. Never.

359
00:31:03,258 --> 00:31:05,588
- Why not? - Don't ask me why.

360
00:31:08,028 --> 00:31:10,928
You're not even telling me the reason. Do I have to listen to you?

361
00:31:10,928 --> 00:31:13,488
I'm telling you not to meddle in my business. Why don't you get it?

362
00:31:13,728 --> 00:31:16,828
This isn't just your business. I'm a victim too.

363
00:31:17,088 --> 00:31:19,358
My safety is being threatened as my personal information got revealed.

364
00:31:19,358 --> 00:31:22,628
I can't even work because I'm getting harassing calls nonstop.

365
00:31:22,628 --> 00:31:23,858
- Also... - I'll compensate you.

366
00:31:24,558 --> 00:31:25,688
How much do you want?

367
00:31:26,828 --> 00:31:29,388
Do you know how much I hate you when you do things like this?

368
00:31:29,728 --> 00:31:32,828
I'm glad that you don't already hate me enough.

369
00:31:34,328 --> 00:31:36,058
How much would be enough?

370
00:31:37,328 --> 00:31:38,358
Tell me.

371
00:31:39,358 --> 00:31:41,758
I'm not doing this because I need money.

372
00:31:41,758 --> 00:31:44,288
I'm saying I can help if revealing the truth will help you.

373
00:31:44,288 --> 00:31:46,558
And I'm telling you that I don't need your help.

374
00:31:46,588 --> 00:31:50,358
For goodness' sake. I just don't get you.

375
00:31:50,488 --> 00:31:53,128
I get that you're a writer, but don't you think you're too moody?

376
00:31:53,188 --> 00:31:55,428
Getting angry like that won't help you resolve the issue.

377
00:31:55,958 --> 00:31:57,788
I've been through things like this many times.

378
00:31:58,388 --> 00:32:00,358
"My neighbor's dog is barking again."

379
00:32:00,958 --> 00:32:02,128
Just think that and this too shall pass.

380
00:32:02,288 --> 00:32:06,428
If we just leave it, it'll end quietly like a contained storm.

381
00:32:06,458 --> 00:32:07,458
So please...

382
00:32:09,288 --> 00:32:10,928
Don't make things worse, please.

383
00:32:11,028 --> 00:32:12,828
Then you should at least make me understand.

384
00:32:13,158 --> 00:32:16,388
You're just telling me not to do it and not to even ask you why.

385
00:32:17,928 --> 00:32:19,388
Are you feeling guilty about something?

386
00:32:19,928 --> 00:32:22,128
Do you actually have a ghost writer in your writing room?

387
00:32:23,328 --> 00:32:26,358
That's not the case. I'm sure you're mad at the false accusations.

388
00:32:26,628 --> 00:32:29,958
You've done nothing wrong. Why can't you say it's not true?

389
00:32:29,958 --> 00:32:31,758
Why are you letting them stomp all over you?

390
00:32:31,758 --> 00:32:33,588
From law to the media, use everything to bring the truth...

391
00:32:33,588 --> 00:32:35,858
Why do you have to help me?

392
00:32:35,858 --> 00:32:38,128
It's because I don't hate you enough yet, okay?

393
00:32:41,888 --> 00:32:43,628
Then do whatever you want.

394
00:32:45,428 --> 00:32:49,258
Instead, don't show up before me ever again.

395
00:32:52,588 --> 00:32:54,258
Ever since I met you,

396
00:32:55,828 --> 00:32:57,658
nothing has been going my way.

397
00:33:01,728 --> 00:33:03,588
I bet that made you hate me enough.

398
00:33:05,258 --> 00:33:06,628
So...

399
00:33:08,058 --> 00:33:12,388
don't try to help me and just turn a blind eye to it.

400
00:33:15,328 --> 00:33:17,228
I'm going to figure it out on my own.

401
00:33:37,528 --> 00:33:41,058
You've done nothing wrong. Why can't you say it's not true?

402
00:33:41,688 --> 00:33:45,758
I'm Mr. Han Se Ju's ghost writer,

403
00:33:46,528 --> 00:33:47,758
Yoo Jin Oh.

404
00:33:48,228 --> 00:33:51,328
I see that you have something writers should not have.

405
00:33:54,958 --> 00:33:57,158
Wouldn't you be in trouble too?

406
00:33:57,328 --> 00:33:59,928
If the police come, they'll ask what I was doing here.

407
00:33:59,928 --> 00:34:01,728
Then I'll have no choice...

408
00:34:01,728 --> 00:34:04,728
but to tell them that I was writing your manuscript in your place.

409
00:34:05,058 --> 00:34:08,958
This is an accident, a mishap I can't laugh about.

410
00:34:09,528 --> 00:34:11,588
It's just a fleeting mistake.

411
00:34:14,928 --> 00:34:17,228
I can make everything go back. I can do it.

412
00:34:17,988 --> 00:34:21,988
Back to the beginning. That will solve everything.

413
00:34:39,558 --> 00:34:43,228
I must write. In order to turn this ridiculous situation around,

414
00:34:43,728 --> 00:34:46,788
I have to write no matter what. On my own, with my own ability.

415
00:34:47,428 --> 00:34:50,488
I must prove to the world that I still got it.

416
00:34:52,858 --> 00:34:54,288
It's not too late yet.

417
00:35:27,398 --> 00:35:29,288
Hey, what's up?

418
00:35:29,588 --> 00:35:31,028
Yes, it's me.

419
00:35:32,658 --> 00:35:34,258
I read the manuscript.

420
00:35:40,428 --> 00:35:42,188
You must've been really stressed out.

421
00:35:43,758 --> 00:35:45,928
Stop beating around the bush and get to the point.

422
00:35:45,928 --> 00:35:49,558
Right, we should be able to say anything to each other.

423
00:35:50,898 --> 00:35:52,858
The manuscript you sent me...

424
00:35:53,428 --> 00:35:55,158
As I was reading it,

425
00:35:55,858 --> 00:35:58,728
I got these icky feelings for some reason.

426
00:35:59,428 --> 00:36:02,288
I can't quite pinpoint it,

427
00:36:02,558 --> 00:36:05,428
but the style of writing is quite stiff. And the storyline...

428
00:36:05,458 --> 00:36:07,898
doesn't pull me in either.

429
00:36:09,188 --> 00:36:10,288
In short,

430
00:36:11,358 --> 00:36:13,188
it doesn't look like it was written by you.

431
00:36:14,188 --> 00:36:16,788
Because of all the gossips that you have a ghostwriter,

432
00:36:16,788 --> 00:36:19,188
you probably couldn't help but feel more pressure unconsciously.

433
00:36:19,858 --> 00:36:22,528
But you know, I can completely understand.

434
00:36:22,528 --> 00:36:24,398
Okay? That being said, I went ahead and...

435
00:36:26,358 --> 00:36:27,758
I told them it'd be put on pause.

436
00:36:32,928 --> 00:36:33,928
Se Ju?

437
00:36:35,128 --> 00:36:36,188
Se Ju?

438
00:36:37,328 --> 00:36:41,188
Oh, sorry. I was actually just about to call you.

439
00:36:42,398 --> 00:36:46,288
I checked and realized that I sent you the wrong file.

440
00:36:46,628 --> 00:36:48,158
Right? I knew it!

441
00:36:49,228 --> 00:36:51,328
Gosh, I thought it was so strange.

442
00:36:51,328 --> 00:36:54,528
I was wondering if you actually had a ghost writer write this.

443
00:36:55,188 --> 00:36:58,588
Hey, just a second. Let me call them and cancel what I said.

444
00:36:58,858 --> 00:37:01,898
- Hey, hold on a second. - Can you send it in 10 minutes?

445
00:37:02,588 --> 00:37:06,058
Well, not really. I'm working out right now.

446
00:37:06,928 --> 00:37:10,158
For me to go back to the writing room and send it... About an hour?

447
00:37:10,158 --> 00:37:12,028
No, about two hours?

448
00:37:12,958 --> 00:37:15,488
Yes. Just give me two hours.

449
00:37:35,058 --> 00:37:37,488
Even though we lost our country,

450
00:37:39,488 --> 00:37:41,958
- no one can take my words away... - If I can't write...

451
00:37:43,188 --> 00:37:45,658
- If I can't write... - If I can't write,

452
00:37:46,828 --> 00:37:48,788
- When Joseon is liberated... - I'll be no different from a ghost.

453
00:37:49,458 --> 00:37:51,228
When Joseon is liberated...

454
00:37:53,288 --> 00:37:56,028
- Even though we lost our country, - If I can't write...

455
00:37:56,028 --> 00:37:59,658
- no one can take my words away. - When Joseon is liberated...

456
00:38:00,058 --> 00:38:02,058
If I can't write...

457
00:38:06,028 --> 00:38:08,228
- What I want to write about is... - Gosh.

458
00:38:08,228 --> 00:38:12,028
- Although we've lost our country... - I'll be no different from a ghost.

459
00:38:24,188 --> 00:38:26,588
Sir, wait! Just a moment, please.

460
00:39:00,658 --> 00:39:01,898
Did you not find it?

461
00:39:03,628 --> 00:39:06,488
Didn't you go outside to find the script you burnt?

462
00:39:08,288 --> 00:39:09,328
Get out,

463
00:39:11,028 --> 00:39:12,288
before I call the police.

464
00:39:13,758 --> 00:39:15,188
This is my last warning.

465
00:39:15,188 --> 00:39:17,028
I have another copy of the script.

466
00:39:27,898 --> 00:39:29,258
If you want it,

467
00:39:30,088 --> 00:39:31,528
I will give it to you.

468
00:39:36,258 --> 00:39:37,258
But,

469
00:39:39,398 --> 00:39:40,898
there is one condition.

470
00:39:43,328 --> 00:39:44,458
Condition?

471
00:39:45,898 --> 00:39:47,588
You sneaky man.

472
00:39:49,028 --> 00:39:51,488
You have no reason or purpose for approaching me.

473
00:39:51,488 --> 00:39:52,928
Yet you have a condition.

474
00:39:55,258 --> 00:39:57,828
I need you to finish this novel.

475
00:39:58,558 --> 00:40:00,788
For giving this script to you,

476
00:40:01,658 --> 00:40:04,328
let me stay here with you.

477
00:40:04,988 --> 00:40:07,558
I will stay here until you finish the novel.

478
00:40:08,398 --> 00:40:09,758
Why would I?

479
00:40:10,428 --> 00:40:14,258
I can barely stop myself from choking you right now.

480
00:40:16,828 --> 00:40:20,588
I have the script for the third week script, and you need it.

481
00:40:22,858 --> 00:40:24,288
Am I wrong?

482
00:40:27,458 --> 00:40:29,128
Why don't you admit it now?

483
00:40:30,228 --> 00:40:32,788
Without me, you cannot go on with the novel.

484
00:40:33,758 --> 00:40:37,128
However, if we come together,

485
00:40:37,458 --> 00:40:39,828
you can finish this novel.

486
00:40:47,398 --> 00:40:48,858
What would you do?

